My Railway deployment is failing because the builder is trying to install Python with mise python@Python, but the log shows:

python-build: definition not found: Python
mise ERROR failed to install core:python@Python


This is happening because my repo has a .python-version file with just Python in it. Railway expects a valid version like python-3.11.9.

👉 Please fix this issue by:

Setting the correct Python version (e.g., python-3.11.9) in either .python-version or runtime.txt.

Making sure the project builds properly on Railway with Node for frontend and Python for backend (Django).

If frontend and backend are separate, configure so that frontend only uses Node, and backend only uses Python (so Railway doesn’t try to install both unnecessarily).{
  "$schema": "https://railway.app/railway.schema.json",
  "deploy": {
    "startCommand": "npm run build && npm run start",
    "healthcheckPath": "/",
    "healthcheckTimeout": 100,
    "restartPolicyType": "ON_FAILURE",
    "restartPolicyMaxRetries": 10
  }
}
